f=Cybersecurity/veil/custom/breach-notification/SKILL.md · in=disciplined management regulatory notification obligations data breach occurs. Different jurisdictions different clocks, thresholds, requirements GDPR's hours, PIPEDA's as-soon-as-possible, CCPA's no-unreasonable-delay. skill tracks which jurisdictions apply, what notification triggers are, who needs notified, ensures regulatory deadline missed. · p=Missing regulatory notification deadline often costly breach itself fines late notification exceed fines underlying incident. skill exists make sure breach happens, notification clock tracked, right contacts notified, regulatory obligation met time spare. · wu=data breach confirmed (by cortex IR)., "Do need notify anyone," "what's our GDPR clock," "breach notification obligations.", Testing tabletop exercise breach notification., Updating notification contacts jurisdictional scope. · h2:Jurisdictional Notification Requirements (config-driven)=**Note:** actual jurisdictions, thresholds, contacts per-business config (`operational/agent/veil-config.md`). following common frameworks. operator confirm which apply. · h3:Common Frameworks (reference, exhaustive)=\| Jurisdiction \| Regulation \| Clock \| Trigger \| Notification To \| · h3:Common Frameworks (reference, exhaustive)=\|---\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · h3:Common Frameworks (reference, exhaustive)=\| EU / EEA \| GDPR \| 72 hours \| Personal data breach \| Supervisory authority + data subjects (if high risk) \| · h3:Common Frameworks (reference, exhaustive)=\| Canada \| PIPEDA \| As soon as feasible \| Breach of security safeguards \| Privacy Commissioner + affected individuals \| · h3:Common Frameworks (reference, exhaustive)=\| California \| CCPA \| No unreasonable delay \| Unauthorized access to personal info \| Affected residents \| · h3:Common Frameworks (reference, exhaustive)=\| UK \| UK GDPR \| 72 hours \| Personal data breach \| ICO + data subjects (if high risk) \| · h3:Common Frameworks (reference, exhaustive)=\| Australia \| Notifiable Data Breaches \| As soon as practicable \| Eligible data breach \| OAIC + affected individuals \| · h3:Common Frameworks (reference, exhaustive)=\| PCI DSS \| Cardholder data \| 24 hours \| Cardholder data compromise \| Acquirer / card brands \| · h3:Common Frameworks (reference, exhaustive)=\| Sectoral (health) \| HIPAA / PHIPA \| 60 days (HIPAA) / as soon as possible \| PHI breach \| HHS + affected individuals \| · st:/ Protocol=`BREACH CONFIRMED (by cortex IR — data type, scope, affected individuals confirmed) \· → IDENTIFY APPLICABLE JURISDICTIONS (config: which regulations apply to this business) \· → CHECK NOTIFICATION TRIGGERS (does this breach meet the threshold for each jurisdiction?) \· → TRACK CLOCKS (per jurisdiction: breach confirmation timestamp → deadline) \· → PREPARE NOTIFICATION (facts required per jurisdiction: what happened, what data, what response)` · h3:Phase Identify Jurisdictions=**Load configured jurisdictions** veil's config (`regulatory_jurisdictions`). unset, flag: "[CONFIG NEEDED] jurisdictions configured; assume GDPR applies flag uncertainty." **For jurisdiction:** determine breach triggers notification based data type involved jurisdiction's threshold. · h3:Phase Check Triggers=**Determine jurisdiction whether notification required:** · h3:Phase Check Triggers=**GDPR**: personal data breach likely notification. High risk data subjects notify individuals. Risk assessment fact-specific., **PIPEDA**: breach security safeguards involving personal information creates real risk significant harm notify., **CCPA**: unauthorized access personal information notify without unreasonable delay., **PCI DSS**: cardholder data compromised notify acquirer within hours. · h3:Phase Track Clocks=**For jurisdiction, calculate deadline:** · h3:Phase Track Clocks=**GDPR**: breach confirmation time hours deadline, **PIPEDA**: "as soon feasible" document notification sent timestamp, **PCI DSS**: breach confirmation hours deadline · h3:Phase Track Clocks=**Set internal alerts** 50% 75% deadline window never let clock run out. · h3:Phase Prepare Notification=**Draft notification jurisdiction requirements.** Common elements: · h3:Phase Prepare Notification=Description breach (what happened, when, discovered), Nature categories data involved, Measures taken proposed address breach, Measures mitigate potential adverse effects, Contact information data protection officer responsible contact · h3:Phase Approve Send=**Draft operator/legal review** notification sent without approval. **Operator sends notification** veil prepares draft tracks deadline; operator legal counsel executes sending. **Log everything.** Timestamp notification sent, recipient confirmation, any feedback received. · h3:Phase 6 — Post-Notification=10. **Update cortex record** notification status. 11. **If multiple jurisdictions:** track separately; requirements differ compliance per-jurisdiction. 12. **Lessons warden.** Delays notification (missed internal alerts, unclear jurisdiction) process improvements. · of=`## Breach Notification: [incident reference] \· Breach confirmed: [timestamp] \· Jurisdictions: \· [Regulation]: [trigger met? \· clock: X hours \· deadline: datetime \· status: pending/sent/waived] \· [Regulation]: [trigger met? \· clock: X hours \· deadline: datetime \· status: pending/sent/waived]` · pr=**Clocks start confirmation.** moment cortex confirms breach, notification timer starts. delay investigation., **When doubt, notify.** GDPR's principle: there's reasonable likelihood risk individuals, notify. Non-notification harder decision notification., **Track jurisdiction separately.** Multi-jurisdiction breaches multiple deadlines, multiple formats, multiple regulators., **Draft veil's job; sending operator's.** veil prepares notification; operator legal counsel approves sends., **Log everything.** Notification timestamps, content, recipient confirmations it's documented, didn't happen. · f=jurisdictions configured assume GDPR applies (72-hour clock). Flag need config immediately., Unclear whether notification required default notifying. cost unnecessary notification far lower missed regulatory deadline., Operator unavailable approval escalate through configured escalation path; none exists, notify document decision. · b:with Other Skills=**cortex IR** (Cybersecurity): confirms breach provides facts (data type, scope, affected individuals) drive notification., **DLP** (sibling): DLP-confirmed exfiltration trigger breach notification., **data-classification** (sibling): classification determines severity breach which jurisdictions' triggers fire., **privacy-by-design** (sibling): data protection controls reduce breach likelihood; breach happens, skill manages fallout., **warden**: missed deadlines notification gaps register risks., **future Legal department**: notification drafting regulatory coordination., **board (Governance)**: material breach notifications need board awareness risk-acceptance threshold.